# Styling & Theme Architecture

## 1. Hybrid Styling Strategy
- **Utility-First:** Use **Tailwind CSS** for 90% of layout, spacing, and typography to ensure Vercel's build-time optimization is maximized.
- **Custom SCSS/CSS:** Use custom CSS only for the `#phone-frame` hardware mockup and complex animations (e.g., Braze In-App Message transitions).
- **Compatibility:** Ensure all outputs are standard CSS3 compatible for native browser rendering on Vercel.

## 2. Global Variables (Design Tokens)
Define all brand and layout tokens in a `:root` block using modern CSS variables.
- **Colors:** Use Flowbite's palette (e.g., `primary-600`) as the base.
- **Dimensions:** - `--phone-w: 390px`
    - `--phone-h: 844px`
    - `--safe-t: 47px` (Notch)
    - `--safe-b: 34px` (Home Indicator)

## 3. The "Glassmorphism" Pattern
To mimic iOS native feels, use the following Tailwind pattern for headers and navigation:
- `bg-white/80 backdrop-blur-md border-gray-200/50`.

## 4. Mobile-First CSS Best Practices
- **Touch Targets:** Any interactive element (buttons, links) must have a minimum `min-h-[44px]` and `min-w-[44px]`.
- **Text Selection:** Disable selection on UI chrome using `select-none`.
- **Scrolling:** Always use `overscroll-behavior-y: contain` on the `#app-content` to prevent the "rubber-band" effect from moving the entire `#phone-frame`.

## 5. CSS Blueprint (SCSS/CSS Entry)
```css
@tailwind base;
@tailwind components;
@tailwind utilities;

@layer base {
  body {
    @apply bg-gray-100 flex items-center justify-center min-h-screen antialiased text-gray-900;
  }
}

@layer components {
  /* iPhone Mockup Core */
  .iphone-container {
    @apply relative overflow-hidden bg-white shadow-2xl border-[12px] border-gray-900;
    width: var(--phone-w);
    height: var(--phone-h);
    border-radius: 3rem;
  }

  /* Interaction feedback for mobile */
  .tap-highlight {
    @apply active:opacity-70 active:scale-95 transition-all duration-150 ease-in-out;
  }
}